{"title_page": "Kovankaya, \u015e\u0131rnak", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image = Assyrian Meer Village.jpg\n| caption = \n}}\n\n'''Kovankaya''' ({{lang-arc|Meer}})<ref name=\"source1\" >{{cite book |author1=Joseph Yacoub |title=Year of the Sword: The Assyrian Christian Genocide, A History |date=2016 |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=9780190694746 |page=194}}</ref> is a village in the district of [[Beyt\u00fc\u015f\u015febap]] of [[\u015e\u0131rnak Province]] in [[Turkey]]. \n\n==History==\n{{expand section|date=April 2020}}\nThe village was historically [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]] but depopulated in June 1994 during the [[Kurdish\u2013Turkish conflict (1978\u2013present)|Kurdish\u2013Turkish conflict]] and subsequently repopulated by [[Kurds]].<ref name=\"source1\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=A\u015firetler raporu |agency=Kaynak Yay\u0131nlar\u0131 |date=1998 |page=156 |language=tr}}</ref> Few Assyrians have returned to the village.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u015e\u0131rnak'ta 11 Ocak'tan beri kay\u0131p olan Keldani \u00e7iftin o\u011fullar\u0131 Papaz Diril: 'Hayatta olduklar\u0131n\u0131 umuyoruz' |url=https://www.bbc.com/turkce/haberler-turkiye-51161166 |accessdate=25 April 2020 |work=BBC News T\u00fcrk\u00e7e |agency=[[BBC]] |date=18 January 2020 |language=tr}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Geography|Kurdistan|Turkey}}\n\n{{coord missing|Turkey}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Meer, Beytussebap}}\n[[Category:Assyrian communities in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Kurdish settlements]]\n[[Category:Populated places in \u015e\u0131rnak Province]]\n\n{{\u015e\u0131rnak-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image = Assyrian Meer Village.jpg\n| caption = \n}}\n\n'''Kovankaya''' ({{lang-arc|Meer}})<ref name=\"source1\" >{{cite book |author1=Joseph Yacoub |title=Year of the Sword: The Assyrian Christian Genocide, A History |date=2016 |publi